On Tue, 29 Apr 2003, Sage Green wrote:

> OK, Dean, I forgot about this idea.  I am cc:ing the list to get their 
> thoughts and input.
> 
> Basic problem:  cannot remove rear brake drum on '72.
> 
> 
> Basic assumption:  adjusting stars are frozen and cannot be backed off.
> 
> 
> Basic solution:   get some movement on brake drum and build on that movement 
> until drum slides off (humor off)
> 
> 
> Questionable Eureka!!:  If you unscrew each rear brake bleeder screw, the 
> wheel cylinder pistons would want to recede into the empty wheel cylinder 
> (brake fluid would drain/shoot/squirt out of wheel cylinder = empty).  this 
> would take the pressure off the brake shoes against the brake drum, and you 
> should be able to whack the sides of the brake drums to encourage the brake 
> shoes to 'back off'
> 
> Barry
